title: DORA | DORA Research Errata
content: This page lists errors and corrections to the Impact of Generative AI in Software Development. To track revisions, report PDFs are stamped with a version number. The current version of the report is v.2025.2. Errata in v.2025.2link click to copy link p. 29 In footnote 2, the link to “AI in software engineering at Google: Progress and the path ahead” is incorrect. It should link to - https://research.google/blog/ai-in-software-engineering-at-google-progress-and-the-path-ahead/ Errata in v.2025.1link click to copy link p. 29 In footnote 2, the link to “AI in software engineering at Google: Progress and the path ahead” is incorrect. It should link to - https://research.google/blog/ai-in-software-engineering-at-google-progress-and-the-path-ahead/ p. 49 The word “acquire” is broken with a line break. The sentence should read “Frame AI as an opportunity for developers to acquire new skills and expand their expertise.” [Corrected in v.2025.2] Have you found an error the Impact of Generative AI in Software Development? Submit a change or correction

metadata.description: DORA is a long running research program that seeks to understand the capabilities that drive software delivery and operations performance. DORA helps teams apply those capabilities, leading to better organizational performance.
